Backtracking is actually recursion + undo , basically you do recursion explore and clean the state afterwards , in more formal terms backtracking is 
controoled recursion + pass by referance

what is controlled recursion ?

We don't blindly call recursion for all states , we identify valid states which can contribute to answer and only call recursion for them. In short we prune invalid states

why pass by refarnce ?

To ensure we dont create unnecessary states , we preserve the state which contributes to answer since we are handling clean up 

Template 

void solve(state &state) { --> pass by ref
    if (base_condition) {
        answer.push_back(state);
        return;
    }

    for (choice in all_choices) {
        if (isValid(choice)) { --> controlling the recursion
            make_choice(choice);
            solve(updated_state);
            undo_choice(choice);   // backtrack
        }
    }
}


